  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Offshore Structural Engineer",
  "description": "<h3>Responsibilities </h3><ul><li>Work scope and technical requirements identification.</li><li>Take part in the technical clarification and prepare discipline proposals.</li><li>Design, review and approval of Structure professional documents, and closure of owner opinions.</li><li>Responsible for coordinating, tracking, implementing and dealing with all kinds of problems in the Structure\ntechnical documents.</li><li>Responsible for preparing and review of technical documents for material bidding of Structure discipline,\nclarification of bid evaluation, vendor drawings review, FAT inspection and\nother procurement technical support work.</li><li>Responsible for the preparation or review of special reports, as well as the review of various calculation results.</li><li>Responsible for site coordination, scheme discussion and other technical support during project\nconstruction.</li><li>Complete other work assigned by Project Manager and Structure department.</li></ul><p></p><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li>Bachelor degree or above</li><li>More than 15 years of experience in offshore engineering (offshore platform, FPSO and semi-submersible platform, etc.) structural design</li><li>Major in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering or structural engineering.</li><li>Familiar with the international standards for offshore structural engineering (API RP-2A, ISO 19901 etc.)</li><li>Familiar with structural engineering works of offshore oil platforms</li><li>Experience with SACS, AutoCAD software to perform structural engineering works</li></ul>",
